                            <comment id="12954027" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2009 20:00:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I guess it makes sense for the routing slip to always stop as it does not aggregate, and its essentially a pipes and filters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just wanted to inform that otherwise adding the option &lt;tt&gt;stopOnException&lt;/tt&gt; should have been preferred such as with splitter / multicast etc.&lt;br/&gt;
As they are capable of aggregating where you can deal with the exception.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12954020" author="janstey" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2009 20:04:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, makes sense. Thats why I added in stopping logic similar to the pipeline processor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
